# Definition Of Done

Every slice must pass all of these before being marked `DONE`.

## Behavior

1. Works end-to-end on QBox.
2. Works end-to-end on QBCore.
3. Happy-path smoke test is documented in the slice mini-brief.

## Quality

4. Automated tests exist where they make sense: economic logic, server validations, formulas, and FSMs.
5. No hardcoded user-facing strings; use `locales/{es,en}.lua`.
6. No hardcoded magic numbers; use `config.lua` or per-domain config files.

## Architecture

7. Respects the 5 Pillars of Bible §3.
8. Respects Bible §9.4 technical anti-patterns.
9. Respects `naming-conventions.mdc`.

## Persistence

10. DB migrations are versioned and rollbackable when the slice touches the DB.

## Documentation

11. Slice mini-brief is updated with what was actually built.
12. ADR is created in `docs/02_DECISIONS.md` for non-obvious architectural decisions.
13. Bible §18 changelog is updated if the slice changed product canon.

## Enforcement

The `/end-slice <SXX>` workflow verifies this checklist and refuses to close if any item is missing.
